Scripting
A shebang is the first line in a script file:
#!/bin/{env}


File Extensions and Conventions
Purpose		Shebang			Extension		Usage
Bash script	#!/bin/bash		.sh		General purpose, Linux default
C Shell script	#!/bin/csh		.csh		Specific C Shell needs
Z Shell script	#!/bin/zsh		.zsh		Modern macOS
Portable script	#!/bin/sh		.sh		Maximum compatibility
Python script	#!/usr/bin/env python3	.py		Python programs
Perl script	#!/usr/bin/env perl	.pl		Perl programs
